    <svcproc graphiccount="1">
        <title>Injection Control Pressure (ICP) System</title>
        <figure id="f3050121" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figj31/j31025.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="256px" box="no"/>
            <caption>ICP closed loop system</caption>
        </figure>
        <para>The ICP system is a closed loop system that uses ICP sensor voltage to provide feedback to the Electronic
            Control Module (ECM). The ECM commands IPR valve duty cycle to open or close to maintain ICP pressure by
            dumping excess high-pressure oil back to the crankcase sump.
        </para>
    </svcproc>
